### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

I use the feature [ngCspNonce](https://angular.dev/best-practices/security#content-security-policy) in my web application (extracted example: https://github.com/ZuInnoTe/spring-boot-angular-example/tree/main/frontend). 

This works without issues if I compile the frontend to development with ngCspNonce (or if I simply do not add ngCspNonce in production mode). However, when I compile to production then I receive the following error in the browser when opening the application:
```
Uncaught SyntaxError: Unexpected end of input
```

It seems to complain about the following script generated by Angular
```
<script nonce = "test" > (() => {
	const CSP_MEDIA_ATTR = 'ngCspMedia';
	const documentElement = document.documentElement; // Listener for load events on link tags.  
	const listener = (e) => {
		const target = e.target;
		if (!target || target.tagName !== 'LINK' || !target.hasAttribute(CSP_MEDIA_ATTR)) {
			return;
		}
		target.media = target.getAttribute(CSP_MEDIA_ATTR);
		target.removeAttribute(CSP_MEDIA_ATTR);
		if (!document.head.querySelector(`link[${CSP_MEDIA_ATTR}]`)) {
			documentElement.removeEventListener('load', listener);
		}
	};
	documentElement.addEventListener('load', listener, true);
})(); < /script>
```

This is browser-independent (the same issue in Firefox and Chromium)



